Description: Fragment of oval handle at neck join to sharpish turn of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Red paint. Clay fine pink-buff. Circular stamp with rose symbol.
Curator's comments: Ink, deleted, '114̣' Name Symmachos. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0211.45.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (246)
